{"id":"5e9c30c19b6559241525dc04","artists":["5e9b68d47a1236eccfeb1e42"],"title":"Exclusive Session: Big Deal","content":"<p><a href=\"https://admin.</p><p>crackintheroad.com/music/7574-exclusive-session-big-deal/attachment/bigdealbig\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-7764\"><img src=\"https://api.crackintheroad.com/uploads/2011/05/bigdealbig.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"bigdealbig\" width=\"900\" height=\"544\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-7764\" srcset=\"https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/05/bigdealbig.jpg 900w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/05/bigdealbig-260x157.jpg 260w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/05/bigdealbig-640x386.jpg 640w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/05/bigdealbig-165x99.jpg 165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></a><br />\nThe <strong>NME Radar </strong>tour is in full swing, packing out every venue that it passes through with <strong>Crack In The Road </strong>favourites <strong>Anna Calvi </strong>and <strong>Grouplove </strong>performing headline and main support sets respectively. However when the tour landed in <strong>Manchester</strong>, it was boy/girl duo <strong>Big Deal </strong>that really caught out attention. Beginning life as ‘<strong>Hard Cheese</strong>‘, <strong>Big Deal </strong>have been gaining the attention of fans and critics alike with their ‘anti twee’ sound, performing stripped down sets which see the band only perform with a guitar each and the harmonies from their vocals. <strong>Crack In The Road </strong>caught up with <strong>Big Deal </strong>before their gig at <strong>Manchester Academy</strong>, and the band were kind enough to let us record a couple of tracks. Enjoy!</p>\n<p><strong>Talk:</strong></p>\n<p><object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" width=\"560\" height=\"349\" codebase=\"https://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\"><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allows